Entry.JapaneseText: おう、さっき燃やした アカトゲサボテンだ。
Entry.EnglishText: Oh, this is that red-thorned cactus you set on fire earlier.

Entry.JapaneseText: ジューシーで歯ごたえもあって、 なかなかウマイぜぇ！
Entry.EnglishText: It's juicy and chewy, so it's pretty good!

Entry.JapaneseText: あ、ボクも食べたい！ ちょうだい！ んぐッ…………
Entry.EnglishText: Oh, I want some too! Pretty please! Nom...

Entry.JapaneseText: ニガーイ！！ ナニコレ！ ニガすぎておいしくないヨ！
Entry.EnglishText: This is bitter!! What the heck! It's so bitter! It's just disgusting!

Entry.JapaneseText: いっちょまえのふりして、まだまだコドモだなぁ。 その苦さが大人の味ってヤツだぜ！
Entry.EnglishText: You're always trying to act grown up, but you're still a kid. That bitterness is what they call an adult's palate!

Entry.JapaneseText: 今度から、<Mao>の食事だけ別に作るとするか…… 「お子様ランチ」ってヤツを。
Entry.EnglishText: From now on, I'm going to make you your own special meal... A kid's meal, that is!
